#Shell
A shell is a special user program that provides an interface for the user to use operating system services. 
user inpuy ----> CLI ----> shell convrts it into os understandable format -----> kernel

#What is a terminal?
A program which is responsible for providing an interface to a user so that he/she can access the shell. 

## sheell scripts 
file containing number of shell commands , which we want to execute them once . it can be done by giving this file as input to shel , it executes all 
these commands and providese the output .
--> by integrating shell commands in scripts it is easy to run number of commands as a batch . write once and execute any time.
--> To avoid repetitive work and automation
--> System admins use shell scripting for routine backups.
--> System monitoring
--> Adding new functionality to the shell etc.

